*The following results can now be proved:*

(*diameter of* "*universe*") &lt; 10,000 (*diameter of earth*),

*and* (*diameter of* "*universe*") &lt;10,000,000,000 *stadia*.

\(1\) Suppose, for brevity, that *d<sub>u</sub>* represents the diameter
of the "universe," *d<sub>s</sub>* that of the sun, *d<sub>e</sub>* that
of the earth, and *d<sub>m</sub>* that of the moon.

By hypothesis, *d<sub>s</sub>* ≯ 30 *d<sub>m</sub>*, \[Assumption 3\]

